The process of returning a copied value back to the caller is namedreturn by value.NomenclatureThe return expression produces the value to be returned. The return value is a copy of that value.A value-returning function will return a value each time it is called.Let’s take a look at a simple function that returns an integer value, and a sample program that calls it:#include <iostream>

// int is the return type
